1
00:00:06,420 --> 00:00:11,420
Alright then, let's choose
the class president for Class 6-1.

2
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:14,380
Is there anyone
who would like to run?

3
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:19,920
Huh? No one? Really?

4
00:00:20,060 --> 00:00:22,030
Is there no one

5
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,840
who wants to run?

6
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:26,630
I think King would be
a good class president.

7
00:00:27,540 --> 00:00:29,020
Hey, knock it off.

8
00:00:30,010 --> 00:00:32,100
Then who else is gonna do it?

9
00:00:33,610 --> 00:00:35,420
There's no one but you!

10
00:00:35,450 --> 00:00:37,660
I agree!

11
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,070
Takaki, what do you think?

12
00:00:41,540 --> 00:00:42,470
I think...

13
00:00:45,410 --> 00:00:47,490
Kobayashi would be better
as class president.

14
00:00:47,820 --> 00:00:48,290
Huh?

15
00:00:48,780 --> 00:00:50,260
Kobayashi?

16
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:52,980
She would definitely
be better than me. Right?

17
00:00:57,020 --> 00:00:58,760
- "Donoko, King"
- That's so messed up!

18
00:00:59,450 --> 00:01:01,030
Hey! Stop messing around!

19
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,010
Hey!

20
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:06,020
No graffiti!
You have to follow the rules.

21
00:01:06,630 --> 00:01:07,630
Oh shoot!

22
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,800
Hurry up!

23
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,250
You guys are too slow!

24
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:15,060
I'm going to tell the teacher on you guys!

25
00:01:21,210 --> 00:01:23,980
"Donoko, King"

26
00:02:16,930 --> 00:02:19,400
"To the Future"

27
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,400
- Take care.
- You too.

28
00:02:46,190 --> 00:02:47,400
"All Recording Files"

29
00:02:55,420 --> 00:02:57,420
Oh, there you are. I'm glad.

30
00:02:57,620 --> 00:02:59,420
- Sorry for coming so suddenly.
Uh...

31
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,630
Iinchou?

32
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,740
Haryu?

33
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:08,290
And Tabo!

34
00:03:12,780 --> 00:03:14,470
Then I want to hear

35
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:16,400
your true feelings.

36
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,020
Huh?

37
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:24,370
I used to like Takaki.

38
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:29,070
"Donoko, King"

39
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,140
- Here we go.
- Alright.

40
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,420
Yeah!

41
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,560
- Let’s go hang out!
- All right!

42
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,170
"Trash"

43
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,200
- Was it okay to put that in the trash?
- Yeah.

44
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,310
That is Donoko's pencil case.

45
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,320
Watch out!

46
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:42,840
Who's inside there?

47
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,740
Yeah!

48
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:50,340
You didn’t know that, did you?

49
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:16,280
THE RIGHT TO JUDGE

50
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:31,290
- Don't release any comments.
- Yes.

51
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:35,240
- Thank you for pointing that out.
- It's blowing up on social media.

52
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,420
We're in a meeting...

53
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,920
I understand what you're saying.

54
00:06:42,380 --> 00:06:45,600
- As for that matter, the editor-in-chief will...
- Sonoko.

55
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,680
Look at this.

56
00:06:50,470 --> 00:06:52,920
- "Sonoko Saruhashi Strikes Back!?"
- What is this?

57
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,860
I don't know the details,

58
00:06:55,110 --> 00:06:56,960
but there is an article blaming you

59
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,480
for what happened to your old classmates.

60
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:01,830
What? That's ridiculous.

61
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:05,460
N one really thinks you're a murderer,

62
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,520
but it's good gossip.

63
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,420
Management is handling it.

64
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:10,300
Handling it how?

65
00:07:10,590 --> 00:07:14,760
The company's reputation is at stake,
so they want you to write a rebuttal.

66
00:07:15,350 --> 00:07:16,450
A rebuttal?

67
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:21,270
They barely let me write anything before,
just used me for gravure shoots...

68
00:07:21,810 --> 00:07:23,140
What about the editor-in-chief?

69
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:25,560
He quit.

70
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:27,420
Quit?

71
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:31,050
Rumor is he got headhunted
by a rival publisher.

72
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:33,050
This might be part of it.

73
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:38,420
No... why...

74
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,700
No point in thinking about it.

75
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:44,420
I'll handle things on our side.
It’s better if you’re not here right now.

76
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,630
- Ms. Shinonome.
- Yeah.

77
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:54,980
This is Shinonome speaking.

78
00:08:00,050 --> 00:08:01,590
She's trying to erase it!

79
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,310
- Even though it's pointless!
- True.

80
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,660
It's not gonna come off anyway.

81
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:14,140
- Poor her.
- What an idiot.

82
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,420
Let's take a break.

83
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:26,590
- Five minutes.
- Okay.

84
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:29,420
Moving on to the next topic.

85
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,460
- Oh! That's your friend.
- Sonoko Saruhashi, the "Too Beautiful Reporter,"

86
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:37,820
is now under suspicion of serial murder.

87
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:40,720
Even as a suspicion, that's shocking.

88
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,770
What is this?

89
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,690
- She's been a leading face
- I'm home.

90
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:48,370
for Shukan Apollo,
known as knowledgeable journalist

91
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:52,500
with strong media presence.

92
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:53,920
I liked her.

93
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:57,420
I’ve heard she was respected
in the industry too.

94
00:08:57,540 --> 00:09:01,660
She first gained attention

95
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:04,740
when a photo in a Shukan Apollo
web article about

96
00:09:04,930 --> 00:09:07,310
a top university soccer team's
drug possession

97
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:11,610
accidentally reflected
her image in the glass.

98
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,960
I saw that.

99
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:17,290
Should've been caught in checks, though.

100
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:20,310
- That photo changed her fate, didn’t it?
- Yes.

101
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:26,370
Then, when her image
went viral as "too beautiful,"

102
00:09:26,450 --> 00:09:30,410
she became the star reporter
of Shukan Apollo, but...

103
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:32,580
It's out now.

104
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,540
What do we do?

105
00:09:36,030 --> 00:09:39,400
She is a public figure,
so investigating her will be tricky.

106
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,640
Well, we'll have to
manage it somehow.

107
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:43,800
I just hope

108
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:50,060
no idiots take advantage of the chaos.

109
00:09:51,370 --> 00:09:52,460
Agreed.

110
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,580
- Thanks for the meal.
- Thank you.

111
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,120
Why is she here?

112
00:10:03,380 --> 00:10:04,920
What is she doing...

113
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:07,230
Isn't this crazy?

114
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:08,500
It has to be.

115
00:10:11,530 --> 00:10:12,690
Our eyes just met.

116
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:20,550
"Now Trending: Sonoko Saruhashi"

117
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:22,250
"The Too-Beautiful Killer"

118
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,720
"Found the killer lol"

119
00:10:43,390 --> 00:10:44,750
This has gotten out of hand.

120
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:47,420
Everyone's going crazy.

121
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:49,420
It's obviously fabricated.

122
00:10:49,590 --> 00:10:51,130
Yeah,

123
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,230
we know that.

124
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,150
- It’s Sonoko Saruhashi.
- Damn, it’s Sonoko Saruhashi.

125
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,330
But to everyone else,

126
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:05,340
the "too-beautiful reporter,"
Sonoko Saruhashi,

127
00:11:05,650 --> 00:11:07,970
became a murder suspect overnight.

128
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,120
What should we do?

129
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:16,640
At this point,

130
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:19,780
the more we move,
the more the public will eat it up.

131
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,740
But we can't just sit back
and do nothing.

132
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,530
There's nothing we can do.

133
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:28,770
For now, all we can do is
endure it and wait.

134
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:45,850
Hey, hey, hey...!

135
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:52,920
Ms. Saruhashi,
please give us a comment!

136
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:55,670
- Excuse me, please get us out of here.
- Ah, yes.

137
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,920
Is what Weekly Shinpo reported true?

138
00:11:58,270 --> 00:12:00,240
Are you really involved in the case?

139
00:12:00,310 --> 00:12:01,920
Are you the murderer?

140
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,460
- Give a proper statement!
- Don’t run away!

141
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:08,460
- Did you take revenge on the bullies?
- You've been blaming others all along!

142
00:12:08,950 --> 00:12:11,420
- Ms. Saruhashi!
- Answer us!

143
00:12:16,430 --> 00:12:18,780
Who's inside there?

144
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,720
Who's inside there?

145
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,760
Who's inside there?

146
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:26,110
Help me!

147
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:30,870
Stop! Stop!

148
00:12:32,570 --> 00:12:34,970
Help me! Open up!

149
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:38,630
Stop! Help me!

150
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:40,160
Help!

151
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,430
Who's inside there?

152
00:12:43,990 --> 00:12:48,900
"Incoming call: Saki Kobayashi"

153
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,990
Where are we headed?

154
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:01,330
Ma'am?

155
00:13:07,090 --> 00:13:10,180
Kanon! That’s not something
kids should be reading.

156
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:14,500
Isn't that the girl who performed
Gon, the Little Fox?

157
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:16,430
Yeah.

158
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:19,700
It was on TV earlier too.
She's okay, right?

159
00:13:21,140 --> 00:13:24,250
- She's not a bad person, is she?
- No.

160
00:13:25,410 --> 00:13:26,260
Right?

161
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,670
Because she is your friend, isn't she?

162
00:13:31,690 --> 00:13:33,220
My friend...

163
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:36,050
Make sure you protect her, okay?

164
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:39,420
- Good night.
- Good night.

165
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,110
Are you okay?

166
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:07,550
I've worked so hard to live my life
so that nothing like that

167
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:10,250
My goal is

168
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:16,120
to live strong so that

169
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:18,370
this never happens to me again.

170
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:20,950
would ever happen again...

171
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,550
And yet...

172
00:14:28,890 --> 00:14:31,550
It's really awful, isn’t it?

173
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,030
People just say
whatever they want.

174
00:14:35,310 --> 00:14:39,020
Are they really so perfect that
they feel entitled to judge someone else?

175
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:43,140
Acting all self-righteous
when it suits them,

176
00:14:43,310 --> 00:14:46,040
putting themselves on a pedestal.

177
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,820
It makes me sick.

178
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,130
Iinchou...

179
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:57,700
Oh, sorry.

180
00:14:58,900 --> 00:15:00,850
Me getting angry won't help.

181
00:15:02,050 --> 00:15:02,770
No, it’s okay.

182
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:08,210
But what are you going to do?
You have your job, don't you?

183
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:11,200
You can’t just leave things like this.

184
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:16,880
The company told me
to write a rebuttal article.

185
00:15:17,830 --> 00:15:18,760
A rebuttal?

186
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:29,390
They want me to write the truth
and prove my innocence.

187
00:15:32,310 --> 00:15:33,540
- But...
- You should write it.

188
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:35,810
Huh?

189
00:15:36,230 --> 00:15:38,420
Because you're not
the one at fault.

190
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:40,810
The ones who bullied you are, right?

191
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:46,210
Let people know what really happened.

192
00:15:49,180 --> 00:15:52,570
But if I do that,
Takaki and the others...

193
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:53,660
Takaki?

194
00:15:56,900 --> 00:16:00,710
It would mean that how they bullied me
would become public.

195
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:05,210
Even if I used only their initials,
they’d be identified right away.

196
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:09,080
And what would happen to

197
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:12,060
Koyama’s company
or Takaki’s family?

198
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,690
So what?

199
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:20,500
Think back. Whose fault was it
in the first place?

200
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:24,950
If it weren't for the bullies,
there wouldn’t be any victims.

201
00:16:25,650 --> 00:16:26,550
Am I wrong?

202
00:16:29,710 --> 00:16:33,170
Sono, you can't let it stay like this.

203
00:16:35,810 --> 00:16:38,130
Let's do the right thing.

204
00:16:40,820 --> 00:16:43,580
It’s okay. No one is
going to blame the victim.

205
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,320
All right. I understand.

206
00:17:02,950 --> 00:17:05,920
"Bar Imakuni"

207
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:23,420
- Sorry for calling you guys out here suddenly.
- No problem.

208
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:25,920
Anyway, are you okay?

209
00:17:26,860 --> 00:17:27,930
Of course you're not.

210
00:17:29,460 --> 00:17:32,530
Alright, Moeka, let's make it
private for tonight.

211
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,000
Turn the sign to closed.

212
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,440
My pleasure!

213
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,940
- Sorry.
- It’s totally fine.

214
00:17:39,770 --> 00:17:41,440
We have something to tell you.

215
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:49,360
"Weekly Shinpo"

216
00:17:51,090 --> 00:17:54,810
It’s wrong that Sono should be hurt
by such a ridiculous article.

217
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:59,420
And the root of all this
goes back to our class...

218
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:05,050
I couldn’t do anything, either.

219
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:07,930
So...

220
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:22,940
The company told me
to write a rebuttal article.

221
00:18:24,260 --> 00:18:25,050
A rebuttal?

222
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:30,020
They want me to say that
I'm not the culprit,

223
00:18:32,170 --> 00:18:34,090
that I was actually
the one being bullied.

224
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,760
To make public everything

225
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,830
that was done to me,
just as it happened.

226
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:44,860
Does that mean

227
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:48,880
you'd be writing about
how we bullied you?

228
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:53,120
Yes.

229
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:59,420
If that’s the case,
then it’ll be our turn next.

230
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:05,460
If it comes to that,
will Tabo's company be okay?

231
00:19:07,410 --> 00:19:11,430
- And King’s family too...
- We probably won’t get off lightly.

232
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,440
- I...
- I think you should

233
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:26,440
write a rebuttal.

234
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:37,660
It’s a lie that
you killed them, right?

235
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,780
You shouldn't take the hit for a lie.

236
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,120
But...

237
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:59,960
it’s true that we bullied you.

238
00:20:04,790 --> 00:20:08,550
If we get attacked for that,
then maybe that's only fair.

239
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,570
So

240
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:18,460
I think

241
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:22,600
you should tell the truth properly.

242
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,130
I thought you’d say that.

243
00:20:27,930 --> 00:20:30,740
It’s okay. I’m ready for it.

244
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,450
Me too.

245
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,270
Don’t worry about us.

246
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:53,660
Just make sure you tell the truth.

247
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:06,940
I'm not going to write a rebuttal article.

248
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:12,450
When someone spreads a rumor,

249
00:21:13,630 --> 00:21:15,580
you answer it with the truth.

250
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:19,560
That’s what’s supposed to be right.

251
00:21:22,580 --> 00:21:26,930
But unfortunately,
in today’s world,

252
00:21:31,050 --> 00:21:32,500
people believe what’s right.

253
00:21:34,610 --> 00:21:36,250
They believe what's entertaining.

254
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:42,900
Whether it's the "too beautiful reporter"
or a so-called murderer...

255
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:51,420
The public always decides
on its own who's good and who's bad.

256
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,040
So...

257
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:58,030
there's no point in it.

258
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:02,570
- But, if things stay like this...
- What we should be doing now

259
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:08,380
isn't to confronting a faceless public
we don't even know.

260
00:22:09,140 --> 00:22:10,040
It's facing the case,

261
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,960
and facing all of you.

262
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,210
No, but...!

263
00:22:19,980 --> 00:22:21,150
So that's your decision?

264
00:22:23,110 --> 00:22:23,860
Yes.

265
00:22:28,130 --> 00:22:29,930
This is all thanks to Iinchou.

266
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:37,530
She's the one who said
we should do the right thing.

267
00:22:38,270 --> 00:22:41,440
Uh, I didn't really...

268
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:43,610
That's our class president!

269
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:47,080
Nobody does it like her!

270
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:50,450
Thank you.

271
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:59,030
The person we should be going after
is whoever's behind this case.

272
00:23:01,940 --> 00:23:03,290
So,

273
00:23:06,630 --> 00:23:07,840
I need your help now

274
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:10,490
more than ever.

275
00:23:16,090 --> 00:23:18,600
- Say the word!
- What was that?

276
00:23:18,870 --> 00:23:20,650
Well... samurai spirit!

277
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:24,030
Really? Right now?

278
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,590
Alright! Then I guess
I'll sing a song!

279
00:23:27,620 --> 00:23:29,790
Alright, Moeka,
they're ready to sing!

280
00:23:30,230 --> 00:23:31,200
Coming right up!

281
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:35,320
The place is all yours tonight,
so don't hold back!

282
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:38,480
The distance between you and me

283
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:41,400
Even with my eyes closed,

284
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:45,570
I can read your expression
just from your voice.

285
00:23:47,540 --> 00:23:49,440
Oh? What's going on?

286
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:52,440
You closing already?
It's still early.

287
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:53,990
It’s private party.

288
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,450
Say no more.

289
00:23:58,510 --> 00:24:01,080
- Go ahead.
- You sure? Thanks.

290
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:04,920
Want a drink?

291
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:07,080
Appreciate it.

292
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:26,940
She always takes the things
that matter most to me.

293
00:24:27,990 --> 00:24:31,450
We are always connected.

294
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:34,440
We always understand
each other without words.

295
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:37,750
The telepathy that connects
the distance between us.

296
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,320
Love is

297
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:41,240
- a cycle of falling and rising.
- "Donoko, King"

298
00:24:41,290 --> 00:24:45,060
Let the gentle breeze
turn your tears into a smile.

299
00:24:45,180 --> 00:24:48,040
Even if we’re apart,
we understand each other without words.

300
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,380
Today, a weekly magazine reported that

301
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:59,110
Education Minister Kato
and Vice Minister Sato are

302
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:02,120
- Wow... Ms. Shinonome,
- involved in a double affair...

303
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:04,340
you were sitting on something this big?

304
00:25:05,060 --> 00:25:06,480
Eh, just luck.

305
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:09,490
I'm looking forward to the follow-up.

306
00:25:09,930 --> 00:25:10,520
Yes.

307
00:25:14,090 --> 00:25:15,020
"Just luck," huh?

308
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,860
That scandal really slowed the posts down.

309
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,870
Politicians finally being useful for once.

310
00:25:26,050 --> 00:25:29,670
They're not gone,
but it's definitely better.

311
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:30,750
Yeah.

312
00:25:33,390 --> 00:25:37,020
Alright, let’s get to work.

313
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:39,330
- Yeah.
- Alright!

314
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:52,950
"Welcome to the Takasato
Elementary Forest!"

315
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,920
"Can we meet?"

316
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:04,470
"I won't see Kind and the others.
I'll never forgive them."

317
00:26:04,510 --> 00:26:06,690
"But Chonmage,
I'm okay with seeing you."

318
00:26:13,070 --> 00:26:14,320
Excuse me.

319
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:16,780
Is Ms. Ohtani here?

320
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:19,950
I couldn’t get her on the phone,
so I decided to come by.

321
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:22,170
Oh, well...

322
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:28,490
actually, we’ve been trying to
reach her too, but no luck.

323
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,160
I see.

324
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,650
Alright. I’ll excuse myself.

325
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:55,240
You’re working hard.

326
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:57,700
Hi.

327
00:26:58,870 --> 00:26:59,610
Oh...

328
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:03,180
Ms. Shinonome!

329
00:27:06,010 --> 00:27:07,460
Just like you said, I followed

330
00:27:07,990 --> 00:27:10,730
the former editor-in-chief,
and I got the shot.

331
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:16,340
Judging by their behavior,
I’m sure they're the source.

332
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,390
This guy?

333
00:27:20,210 --> 00:27:21,390
But who is it?

334
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,850
Looks kinda familiar.

335
00:27:31,540 --> 00:27:33,150
"Dad"

336
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:35,350
- How old is your kid?
- Hmm?

337
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:38,940
She is ten, in 4th grade.

338
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:41,580
4th grade, huh...

339
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:46,160
- We were at that age too.
- Yeah...

340
00:27:47,410 --> 00:27:50,280
You saved a dog in the river.

341
00:27:50,650 --> 00:27:52,890
Wait? Was that in 5th grade?

342
00:27:53,450 --> 00:27:54,550
Ah...

343
00:27:55,030 --> 00:27:56,660
I saw you being interviewed on TV.

344
00:27:57,920 --> 00:28:01,230
I thought "This guy isn't just
goofing off in class all the time,

345
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,230
he can actually do something."

346
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:07,250
But what happened to
that dog afterward?

347
00:28:09,940 --> 00:28:10,700
Who knows...

348
00:28:12,950 --> 00:28:16,160
Sorry. I just showed up
and started rambling,

349
00:28:17,390 --> 00:28:20,640
No worries. I actually
wanted to thank you too.

350
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:22,900
Thank me?

351
00:28:23,990 --> 00:28:24,970
For Sonoko.

352
00:28:25,910 --> 00:28:26,680
Thank you.

353
00:28:31,620 --> 00:28:36,190
When that article came out,
I couldn’t do anything.

354
00:28:39,340 --> 00:28:40,520
I mean,

355
00:28:42,110 --> 00:28:44,920
it's my own fault for being a bully
back then, so I get it.

356
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:48,700
I know nothing I do now
can make up for it.

357
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:50,930
So...

358
00:28:54,060 --> 00:28:56,120
I’m glad you were there.

359
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:06,530
When I saved that dog,

360
00:29:07,490 --> 00:29:09,010
I was such a show-off on TV.

361
00:29:09,890 --> 00:29:11,140
But then you told me,

362
00:29:12,410 --> 00:29:18,740
"You should've
contacted an adult first."

363
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:23,750
Did I say that?

364
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:30,820
Honestly, I was probably
a little annoyed at that time.

365
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:34,190
But then my mom said
the exact same thing to me later.

366
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:37,340
So...

367
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:39,980
King would be a good class president.

368
00:29:41,010 --> 00:29:42,710
I agree!

369
00:29:44,030 --> 00:29:46,070
Takaki, what do you think?

370
00:29:46,930 --> 00:29:48,100
I think...

371
00:29:51,090 --> 00:29:53,400
Kobayashi would be
better as class president.

372
00:29:53,670 --> 00:29:56,090
- Huh?
- Kobayashi?

373
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:58,180
She would be
definitely better than me.

374
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,980
Hey, take the cleaning seriously.

375
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:06,800
- You have to do it right.
- Okay...

376
00:30:06,850 --> 00:30:08,770
We were just kids back then and

377
00:30:10,170 --> 00:30:11,540
didn’t understand anything.

378
00:30:12,370 --> 00:30:14,160
Oh no, here comes Iinchou!

379
00:30:14,470 --> 00:30:16,580
Hurry up! You’re too slow!

380
00:30:16,710 --> 00:30:18,580
Hurry!

381
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:21,120
I’m going to tell the teacher on you guys!

382
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:26,560
You always called out
what was wrong.

383
00:30:29,810 --> 00:30:33,650
It takes courage to
stand up for what's right.

384
00:30:33,690 --> 00:30:35,500
I only realized
that when I grew up.

385
00:30:36,730 --> 00:30:38,670
Even if you know it,
it's not easy to do.

386
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:46,320
But you always said it anyway.

387
00:30:48,170 --> 00:30:49,210
Yeah...

388
00:30:50,590 --> 00:30:51,630
So,

389
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:56,700
I’m glad you were
|our class president.

390
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:04,440
A bit late for that,
don't you think?

391
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:06,880
True.

392
00:31:16,390 --> 00:31:17,910
Alright, I’m heading out.

393
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:21,470
- Did you have something to talk about?
- No, not really.

394
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:24,850
Besides, I'm meeting up
with Sono after this.

395
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:25,920
Oh?

396
00:31:26,580 --> 00:31:28,340
Thanks to that politician's scandal,

397
00:31:28,550 --> 00:31:30,340
the heat is off her.

398
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,340
So, it feels like a celebration.

399
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,460
Iinchou.

400
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,210
Thank you.

401
00:31:47,300 --> 00:31:51,050
You know you've really changed.

402
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:02,320
"Imakuni"

403
00:32:05,110 --> 00:32:06,720
Hi. What's up?

404
00:32:08,570 --> 00:32:10,850
I’m glad I made it
in time for the last one.

405
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:12,950
Sorry for dragging you along.

406
00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:14,370
It's totally fine.

407
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:19,890
Iinchou?

408
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:24,990
Oh, sorry. Could you
stay with me a little longer?

409
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,850
"Bar Imakuni"

410
00:32:34,950 --> 00:32:36,130
My name is Shinonome.

411
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:38,950
- Oh...
- Thank you for your cooperation this time.

412
00:32:39,070 --> 00:32:39,990
No problem.

413
00:32:40,550 --> 00:32:42,780
- Please feel free to use the place.
- Thank you.

414
00:32:49,470 --> 00:32:51,700
- Huh?
- Okay. Let me know when you’re done.

415
00:32:53,210 --> 00:32:54,740
Sorry to drag you out here.

416
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:57,960
- I’m Shinonome with Shukan Apollo.
- Oh...

417
00:32:59,170 --> 00:33:01,860
There’s actually a photo
I'd like you to see.

418
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,590
The recent article about Saruhashi

419
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:14,840
was written by our former
editor-in-chief at his new job.

420
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:19,100
And the source who fed him
the info was this person.

421
00:33:19,850 --> 00:33:21,600
- Huh?
- What? No way.

422
00:33:22,140 --> 00:33:23,840
Iinchou was selling us out?

423
00:33:24,380 --> 00:33:26,600
Who is Iinchou?

424
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:28,040
Oh, sorry...

425
00:33:28,260 --> 00:33:31,060
Her name’s Saki Kobayashi.
She was our classmate.

426
00:33:31,860 --> 00:33:32,990
Kobayashi?

427
00:33:33,930 --> 00:33:35,500
But why would she do that?

428
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:38,360
I don't know.

429
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:42,480
She said she was going to
meet Sonoko later.

430
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,370
What?

431
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:08,240
She's not picking up.

432
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:09,150
What?

433
00:34:19,850 --> 00:34:21,420
"College Soccer Drug Scandal Exposed"

434
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:24,460
This was Sonoko's first big scoop.

435
00:34:25,090 --> 00:34:27,760
Oh, the one where she got
the whole "too beautiful" thing.

436
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:29,930
Take a look at this photo.

437
00:34:31,170 --> 00:34:33,590
He was the ace
on his college soccer team,

438
00:34:33,750 --> 00:34:35,590
even picked for the national team.

439
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:40,620
Then a teammate got busted for drugs,
the coach tried to cover it up,

440
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:44,240
and the public backlash was brutal.
He stepped down form the national team.

441
00:34:45,210 --> 00:34:47,710
His name is Haruki Kobayashi.

442
00:34:48,890 --> 00:34:50,000
Kobayashi?

443
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:52,620
Wait... then does that mean?

444
00:34:54,970 --> 00:34:56,800
Where are we?

445
00:34:57,210 --> 00:34:59,580
- This is where my brother is.
- Oh.

446
00:35:00,580 --> 00:35:02,080
He was six years younger than me,

447
00:35:02,860 --> 00:35:07,400
loved soccer since he was a kid and
always said he'd play for the national team someday.

448
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:10,530
I didn't know that.

449
00:35:10,910 --> 00:35:12,240
He killed himself.

450
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,530
Because of you.

451
00:35:26,070 --> 00:35:27,720
I think Ms. Kobayashi

452
00:35:27,780 --> 00:35:32,930
gave info on those incidents
as revenge for losing her brother.

453
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,450
But if that’s the case,

454
00:35:35,540 --> 00:35:38,280
wouldn’t that revenge have ended
when the article came out?

455
00:35:38,860 --> 00:35:41,550
Maybe she felt
the revenge wasn’t enough.

456
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:43,090
Don’t mess with me.

457
00:35:43,130 --> 00:35:44,880
- Where are you going?
- I don't know,

458
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:46,570
-but let's get in the car.
- Wait a moment.

459
00:35:48,700 --> 00:35:52,100
Today is the anniversary
of her brother's death.

460
00:35:54,980 --> 00:36:01,220
"The Kobayashi Family Grave"

461
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:04,970
My brother was innocent.

462
00:36:08,190 --> 00:36:11,080
The ones at fault were
the people who did drugs,

463
00:36:12,330 --> 00:36:14,260
and the ones who
tried to cover it up, right?

464
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:20,780
But they used
his photo in the article.

465
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,520
Because of that,

466
00:36:24,100 --> 00:36:27,050
he kept getting attacked
with things that weren't even true.

467
00:36:28,010 --> 00:36:29,650
He didn't do anything.

468
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:33,000
Before long,

469
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:36,590
people were spreading it
like he was the one who used drugs.

470
00:36:37,730 --> 00:36:41,180
He lost everything.

471
00:36:45,140 --> 00:36:48,440
That’s... I only reported on

472
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:51,170
- the drugs and the cover-up...
- Yeah. I'm sure you did.

473
00:36:52,310 --> 00:36:54,400
That’s why you get to
act like the victim, right?

474
00:36:59,950 --> 00:37:03,210
But you're the one who caused it.

475
00:37:06,210 --> 00:37:09,100
He kept saying

476
00:37:09,930 --> 00:37:12,330
he was innocent
and had nothing to do with it.

477
00:37:13,410 --> 00:37:14,650
He told the school.

478
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:16,380
He told the public.

479
00:37:17,540 --> 00:37:21,430
But no one listened.

480
00:37:23,260 --> 00:37:24,790
It’s all because of you!

481
00:37:26,350 --> 00:37:29,610
- I...
- What, you were bullied?

482
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:31,740
So you're the victim?

483
00:37:33,750 --> 00:37:39,020
You should've stayed locked up
in there your whole life.

484
00:37:48,050 --> 00:37:49,180
If you had,

485
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:53,120
he wouldn’t have died!

486
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,590
You really thought

487
00:37:57,040 --> 00:38:00,250
you wear the poor kid
who got bullied all the time, didn't you?

488
00:38:00,770 --> 00:38:01,660
You weren't.

489
00:38:01,990 --> 00:38:03,660
You were the one bullying people!

490
00:38:04,380 --> 00:38:06,260
You bullied someone to death!

491
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:10,000
So you don't get to blame anyone.

492
00:38:10,370 --> 00:38:12,300
And you don't get to play the victim.

493
00:38:12,710 --> 00:38:14,240
You’re the perpetrator!

494
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,110
I...

495
00:38:29,790 --> 00:38:32,400
I'm going to do what’s right.

496
00:38:35,510 --> 00:38:36,660
I...

497
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:42,760
That's our class president!

498
00:38:42,950 --> 00:38:45,160
Nobody does it like her!

499
00:38:45,620 --> 00:38:46,530
Yeah.

500
00:38:47,870 --> 00:38:48,920
Thank you,

501
00:38:50,750 --> 00:38:51,620
Iinchou.

502
00:38:57,910 --> 00:39:00,480
I’m glad you were
our class president.

503
00:39:02,710 --> 00:39:07,940
She's the one who said
we should do the right thing.

504
00:39:10,450 --> 00:39:12,750
Kobayashi would be better
as class president.

505
00:39:12,910 --> 00:39:15,130
- Huh?
- Kobayashi?

506
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:17,360
She is definitely better than me.

507
00:39:17,490 --> 00:39:20,170
Then It’s decided.
Kobayashi is our class president.

508
00:39:59,060 --> 00:40:00,440
- Sono!
- Shino...

509
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:03,650
You...

510
00:40:04,290 --> 00:40:05,010
Tabo!

511
00:42:07,730 --> 00:42:08,360
What?

512
00:42:09,430 --> 00:42:10,690
You've had a rough time.

513
00:42:11,940 --> 00:42:13,550
But, at least you're safe.

514
00:42:15,420 --> 00:42:16,860
You're a detective?

515
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:19,050
Just a humble public servant.

516
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:31,810
What's going to

517
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:36,430
happen to Iinchou...
to Kobayashi?

518
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:39,710
She’ll be in custody for a while.

519
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:45,340
Even if she gets out,
people will still see her as a criminal.

520
00:42:47,170 --> 00:42:48,640
It's not gong to be easy.

521
00:42:52,050 --> 00:42:53,070
I see.

522
00:42:56,420 --> 00:42:57,790
All right.

523
00:43:05,210 --> 00:43:10,290
Toshio Takeda,
Emi Nakajima, Kanta Sakurai.

524
00:43:13,790 --> 00:43:19,110
The three who died were
all bullying you, correct?

525
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:25,700
And...

526
00:43:28,500 --> 00:43:30,800
there are three left.

527
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:34,360
That right?

528
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:40,010
Relax.

529
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:43,520
I don’t think you’re the culprit.

530
00:43:45,650 --> 00:43:53,940
But when four people around you end up dead,
we can’t not ask questions.

531
00:44:00,060 --> 00:44:00,600
Huh?

532
00:44:03,820 --> 00:44:05,230
